.compozy/tasks/agent-soul/adrs/adr-005.md:1:# ADR-005: Defer HEARTBEAT.md to a Separate Runtime Policy Spec
.compozy/tasks/agent-soul/adrs/adr-005.md:13:`SOUL.md` describes who an agent is and how it behaves. `HEARTBEAT.md` describes what an agent should do when it wakes, how it handles recurring checks, and how heartbeat-driven work should run. Competitor systems show `HEARTBEAT.md` quickly crosses into scheduling, wake coalescing, liveness classification, task ownership, API calls, and model-driven background turns.
.compozy/tasks/agent-soul/adrs/adr-005.md:15:AGH already has separate authorities for task-run lease heartbeat, session activity heartbeat, scheduler sweep/notify/recovery, and AGH Network greet presence. Mixing `HEARTBEAT.md` into the Agent Soul feature risks creating a hidden workflow engine in Markdown or bypassing `ClaimNextRun`.
.compozy/tasks/agent-soul/adrs/adr-005.md:19:`HEARTBEAT.md` is explicitly out of scope for the Agent Soul TechSpec. The Agent Soul feature will not implement recurring model-driven heartbeat turns, heartbeat task parsing, wake scheduling, task queue behavior, lease heartbeat changes, scheduler claim behavior, or AGH Network presence changes.
.compozy/tasks/agent-soul/adrs/adr-005.md:21:Any future `HEARTBEAT.md` or wake policy work must be specified separately and must preserve `task_runs` and `ClaimNextRun` as the authoritative executable work and claim path.
.compozy/tasks/agent-soul/adrs/adr-005.md:27:### Alternative 1: Implement HEARTBEAT.md Together with SOUL.md
.compozy/tasks/agent-soul/adrs/adr-005.md:34:### Alternative 2: Add HEARTBEAT.md as Prompt-Only Guidance
.compozy/tasks/agent-soul/adrs/adr-005.md:36:- **Description**: Let `HEARTBEAT.md` be a non-authoritative checklist in prompt context.
.compozy/tasks/agent-soul/adrs/adr-005.md:55:- The future work may be expected soon because competitor systems expose `HEARTBEAT.md`; the TechSpec must name it explicitly as deferred, not forgotten.
.compozy/tasks/agent-soul/adrs/adr-005.md:59:- Mention `HEARTBEAT.md` only in Out of Scope and Future Work sections.
.compozy/tasks/agent-soul/task_04.md:16:Wire resolved Soul profiles into runtime context, session lifecycle, prompt assembly, explicit refresh, spawn semantics, and task claim provenance. This task is the behavioral integration point for `SOUL.md`, while preserving existing task-run lease and orchestration authorities.
.compozy/tasks/agent-soul/task_04.md:24:- NO WORKAROUNDS: do not make `SOUL.md` a task queue, heartbeat, liveness, network presence, or capability authority.
.compozy/tasks/agent-soul/task_04.md:34:- MUST preserve spawn semantics: spawned sessions use the target agent's own `SOUL.md` plus explicit spawn overlays, with no implicit parent Soul inheritance.
.compozy/tasks/agent-soul/task_04.md:35:- MUST ensure invalid existing `SOUL.md` fails closed consistently across session start, refresh, and task claim.
.compozy/tasks/agent-soul/task_04.md:48:Treat the resolver and persisted snapshots from tasks 01-03 as the only Soul authority. The task claim path must use already-resolved snapshot data and must not read `SOUL.md` while claiming work.
