.compozy/tasks/agent-soul/adrs/adr-011.md:13:OpenClaw supports heartbeat cadence, target, light context, isolated sessions, and active hours. Those controls are useful, but AGH already has separate config authorities for session supervision, scheduler behavior, and network greet intervals. Allowing `HEARTBEAT.md` to directly define daemon timing would make a prompt artifact a scheduler.
.compozy/tasks/agent-soul/adrs/adr-011.md:19:`HEARTBEAT.md` may express preferences inside those bounds, such as quiet-window preference, wake summary, prompt/reentry guidance, and context projection hints. It cannot redefine `[session.supervision]`, scheduler intervals, task lease duration, or `[network] greet_interval`.
.compozy/tasks/agent-soul/adrs/adr-011.md:31:### Alternative 1: Put Cadence and Delivery Fully in HEARTBEAT.md
.compozy/tasks/agent-soul/adrs/adr-011.md:40:- **Description**: Use `HEARTBEAT.md` only as checklist/reentry guidance.
.compozy/tasks/agent-soul/adrs/adr-004.md:17:Spawned sessions will not implicitly inherit the parent session's `SOUL.md`. A spawned session uses the target agent's own resolved `SOUL.md`, if present, plus explicit spawn overlays such as `spawn_role` and `prompt_overlay`.
.compozy/tasks/agent-soul/adrs/adr-004.md:55:- Resolve target agent soul at spawn/session creation.
