.compozy/tasks/agent-soul/adrs/adr-009.md:1:# ADR-009: Separate Session Health From HEARTBEAT.md
.compozy/tasks/agent-soul/adrs/adr-009.md:15:The missing runtime primitive is explicit idle session health/presence for deciding whether a session is alive, attachable, and eligible for synthetic wake.
.compozy/tasks/agent-soul/adrs/adr-009.md:24:- Agent `HEARTBEAT.md` Wake Policy: authored reentry/wake guidance.
.compozy/tasks/agent-soul/adrs/adr-009.md:26:`HEARTBEAT.md` consumes session health/presence but does not implement or replace liveness. If the current runtime lacks sufficient idle health data, the implementation must add or reinforce metadata-only `session.health` / `session.liveness` before using the policy for wake decisions.
.compozy/tasks/agent-soul/adrs/adr-009.md:32:### Alternative 1: Fold Session Health Into HEARTBEAT.md
.compozy/tasks/agent-soul/adrs/adr-009.md:34:- **Description**: Let `HEARTBEAT.md` define when a session is healthy or stale.
.compozy/tasks/agent-soul/adrs/adr-009.md:41:- **Description**: Treat AGH Network greet as session health.
.compozy/tasks/agent-soul/adrs/adr-009.md:52:- `HEARTBEAT.md` remains prompt/policy, not liveness.
.compozy/tasks/agent-soul/adrs/adr-007.md:1:# ADR-007: Treat HEARTBEAT.md as Advisory Wake Policy
.compozy/tasks/agent-soul/adrs/adr-007.md:13:`HEARTBEAT.md` has overloaded meanings in reference systems. OpenClaw uses it to shape periodic agent turns, Paperclip uses it as adapter-specific loop instructions, and Hermes uses heartbeat mainly for runtime liveness and durable run ownership.
.compozy/tasks/agent-soul/adrs/adr-007.md:15:AGH already has distinct heartbeat authorities: task-run lease heartbeat, session activity supervision, scheduler wake/sweep, synthetic prompt reentry, and AGH Network greet presence. Introducing `HEARTBEAT.md` as another heartbeat authority would confuse ownership, liveness, and scheduling.
.compozy/tasks/agent-soul/adrs/adr-007.md:19:`HEARTBEAT.md` v1 is an optional authored wake-policy artifact. It may influence synthetic wake/reentry guidance, prompt summary, and policy evaluation for already eligible sessions. It must not create work, create sessions, auto-spawn agents, run an independent loop, renew task-run leases, update session activity, or alter network peer presence.
.compozy/tasks/agent-soul/adrs/adr-007.md:27:- **Description**: Let `HEARTBEAT.md` trigger daemon-created heartbeat sessions when no session is active.
.compozy/tasks/agent-soul/adrs/adr-007.md:45:- Allows a useful `HEARTBEAT.md` artifact without hidden workflow semantics.
.compozy/tasks/agent-soul/task_01.md:13:Create the backend foundation for optional `SOUL.md` files as authored agent identity context. This task defines config, parsing, validation, diagnostics, digesting, and projection limits before any runtime surface consumes the resolved profile.
