.compozy/tasks/agent-soul/adrs/adr-002.md:13:Competitor evidence shows three patterns. OpenClaw injects `SOUL.md` as bounded prompt context and uses separate narrow structured identity. Hermes loads, scans, truncates, and places `SOUL.md` in the first system-prompt slot. Paperclip keeps `SOUL.md` as a sibling file referenced by `AGENTS.md`, which risks the file existing without actually being in prompt context.
.compozy/tasks/agent-soul/adrs/adr-002.md:19:AGH will resolve valid `SOUL.md` content directly and deterministically into the agent prompt path. AGH will also expose:
.compozy/tasks/agent-soul/adrs/adr-002.md:36:- **Description**: Inject `SOUL.md` into prompt but expose no structured read model.
.compozy/tasks/agent-soul/adrs/adr-002.md:50:- **Description**: Inject `AGENT.md` and tell the model to read `SOUL.md`.
.compozy/tasks/agent-soul/adrs/adr-002.md:53:- **Why rejected**: AGH should guarantee applied persona context when `SOUL.md` is valid.
.compozy/tasks/agent-soul/adrs/adr-003.md:17:AGH will resolve and validate `SOUL.md` during agent profile loading. It will snapshot the resolved soul digest/profile at session start and snapshot the active digest/profile again at task-run claim time. AGH will not silently reload `SOUL.md` during active sessions or active task runs.
.compozy/tasks/agent-soul/adrs/adr-003.md:19:Changes to `SOUL.md` take effect for new sessions and new task-run claims. Existing sessions or runs can refresh only through an explicit reload/refresh operation.
.compozy/tasks/agent-soul/adrs/adr-003.md:21:Task-run claim provenance is copied from the claiming session's already-persisted `sessions.soul_snapshot_id` and `sessions.soul_digest`. `ClaimNextRun` performs no `SOUL.md` resolution, parsing, validation, digesting, path traversal, or filesystem I/O. Claims without a session snapshot omit the persisted `soul` metadata block and use a typed internal diagnostic sentinel instead of resolving from disk.
.compozy/tasks/agent-soul/adrs/adr-003.md:29:- **Description**: Read and apply `SOUL.md` before every model call.
.compozy/tasks/agent-soul/adrs/adr-006.md:15:That read-only posture protected authority boundaries, but it did not satisfy AGH's extensible-and-agent-manageable product premise. `SOUL.md` is an authored agent identity file. If AGH can validate and resolve it, AGH should also provide the safe path to create, update, delete, inspect history, and roll it back.
