.compozy/tasks/agent-soul/qa/peer-review-message-round2.md:9:      "issue": "The migration version is never anchored. Step 2 says 'Add global DB migration for heartbeat snapshots, revisions, wake state/events, and session health fields or table.' The phrase 'fields or table' is two different schema shapes; the data model section actually lists `session_health` as a standalone table with `session_id PK`. Two implementers will produce two different migrations; only one matches the data model.",
.compozy/tasks/agent-soul/qa/peer-review-message-round2.md:32:      "suggested_fix": "Either add `agh agent heartbeat refresh <agent> --session <id>` plus HTTP/UDS/Host API counterparts, or remove 'explicit refresh' from Flow step 4 and document explicitly that policy snapshots are evaluated on each wake (not pinned per session). Pick one model and lock it down with DTOs."
.compozy/tasks/agent-soul/qa/peer-review-message-round2.md:51:      "issue": "Testing Approach lists no reopen-after-restart test for the four new tables, no `-race`/concurrency test for wake coalescing (a known race-prone surface per OpenClaw analysis), no test that asserts `ClaimNextRun` and `HeartbeatRunLease` paths perform zero file I/O on `HEARTBEAT.md`, and no parity assertion that wake_state row writes cannot be reached from `internal/task` or `internal/scheduler` (i.e., the 'no parallel queue' invariant). The Verification subsection lists `make verify` but omits `make codegen-check` (mandatory after contract additions) and CLI docs regeneration.",
.compozy/tasks/agent-soul/qa/peer-review-message-round2.md:57:      "section": "Config Lifecycle + HEARTBEAT.md format",
.compozy/tasks/agent-soul/qa/peer-review-message-round2.md:114:  "summary": "The architectural shape is right — `HEARTBEAT.md` correctly stays advisory, `task_runs`/`ClaimNextRun` are preserved, side tables are not queues, managed authoring mirrors Soul, and ADR-005's deferral is honored — but the spec caries multiple L-012 prose-only gaps (missing interface signatures for AuthoringService/SnapshotStore/HealthService/scheduler-integration/synthetic-prompt, ambiguous 'fields or table' language, undefined CAS field shape, unspecified migration version, undefined digest algorithm) that will trigger heavy review rework, and three load-bearing safety properties (active-prompt race serialization, wake/health row lifecycle, reopen-after-restart + race tests) are not pinned down. Lock the data-model and interface signatures, enumerate the missing tests, and add the explicit refresh surface decision before approval."
